APPLE REVIEW REJECTION-Д ХАРИУЛАХ ЗАГВАР
================================================================================

Guideline 5.1.1 - Data Collection and Storage буюу 5.1.2 - Data Use and Sharing:

Hi,

Thank you for your feedback. We use location data solely for delivery route
optimization and GPS-verified delivery confirmation, which is the core
functionality of our last-mile delivery management app.

Here's how we use location:

1. ROUTE OPTIMIZATION: When delivery drivers receive a batch of orders, we use
   their current GPS location to sort delivery addresses from nearest to farthest.
   Without this, drivers cannot efficiently navigate their deliveries.

2. DELIVERY GPS STAMP: When a driver marks an order as delivered, we record
   their GPS coordinates as verifiable proof that they were at the correct
   customer location. This protects both drivers and the company from disputes.

3. DISTANCE DISPLAY: We show drivers the distance (km) to each customer address
   so they can prioritize their route effectively.

Here's how we use the camera:

4. DELIVERY PROOF PHOTO: Drivers can optionally take a photo when completing a
   delivery as additional proof of successful handoff. This is accessed only when
   the driver explicitly taps the camera button.

IMPORTANT:
- We do NOT use background location tracking
- We use "When In Use" permission ONLY
- Location is accessed ONLY when the driver is actively using delivery features
- Camera is accessed ONLY when driver intentionally taps the photo button
- This is an enterprise delivery management app where location and photo proof
  are standard industry practices for last-mile delivery verification

Please let us know if you need any additional information or a demo video
showing these features.

Best regards,
Maximus Delivery Team

